 fish (1997) Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 54, pp. 1504-1512; Megard, R.O., Settles, J.C., Boyer, H.A., Combs, W.S., Light, Secchi disks, and trophic states (1980) Limnology and Oceanography, 25, pp. 373-377; Melnik, N.G., Bondarenko, N.A., Belykh, O.I., Distribution of pelagic invertebrates near a thermal bar in Lake Baikal (2006) Hydrobiologia, 568, pp. 69-76; Melnik, N.G., Sheveleva, N.G., Pomazkova, G.I., Distribution of planktonic copepods of Lake Baikal (1998) Journal of Marine Systems, 15, pp. 149-153; O'Reilly, C.M., Alin, S.R., Plisnier, P.D., Cohen, A.S., McKee, B.A., Climate change decreases aquatic ecosystem productivity of Lake Tanganyika, Africa (2003) Nature, 424, pp. 766-768; Patalas, K., Patterns in zooplankton distribution and their causes in North American great lakes (1990) Large Lakes: Ecological Structure and Function, pp. 440-458. , In: (eds Tilzer MM, Serruya C) Springer-Verlag, Berlin; Patalas, K., Salki, A., Crustacean Plankton in Lake Winnipeg: Variation in space and time as a function of lake morphology, geology, and climate (1992) Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 49, pp. 1035-1059; Peterson, B.J., Holmes, R.M., McClelland, J.W., Increasing river discharge to the Arctic Ocean (2002) Science, 298, pp. 2171-2173; Preisendorfer, R.W., Secchi disk science - Visual optics of natural-waters (1986) Limnology and Oceanography, 31, pp. 909-926; Press, W.H., Teukolsky, S.A., Vetterling, W.T., Flannery, B.P., (1994) Numerical Recipes in C: The Art of Scientific Computing, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; Prowse, T.D., Wrona, F.J., Reist, J.D., Gibson, J.J., Hobbie, J.E., Levesque, L.M.J., Vincent, W.F., Climate change effects on hydroecology of Arctic freshwater ecosystems (2006) Ambio, 35, pp. 347-358; Qian, S., Chen, D., (1996) Joint Time-Frequency Analysis: Methods and Applications, , Prentice-Hall Inc., Upper Saddle River, NJ; Quayle, W.C., Peck, L.S., Peat, H., Ellis-Evans, J.C., Harrigan, P.